Resource Associator: KORA identifier for the Resource record that this Pages record is part of.ÊThis Pages record contains a digital file and technical metadata for 1 scanned page of the referenced Resource.
Resource Identifier: Unique identifier given to the original archival resource that has been scanned. This is the same as RESOURCE.Resource Identifier.For Isthmia: resource dependent code that uniquely identifies a an artifact or archival document
Format: Digital or electronic format of the access or distribution file of the resource.
Type: Broad term describing the nature or genre of digital file
Page Identifier: Unique numeric or alphanumeric identification; Alpha/numeric character string of file name including file extension.
Scan Number: Number indicating the scan sequence for a resource
Image Upload: Upload jpeg file of scanned Archival Object.
Scan Specifications: Description of the dimensions, resolution, type of digitization and any other information pertinent to the creation of the electronic file.
Scan Equipment: Name or other unique identifier of the device used to create an electronic file.
Scan Date: Production date of the electronic file, expressed in yyyy/mm/dd format
Scan Creator: Name or other unique identification of a known person responsible for the creation of the electronic file.
Scan Creator Status: Information concerning whether the identification of a known person may appear in a publicly accessible format.
Rights: Information about rights management; may include copyright and other intellectual property statements required for use regarding the resource and/or its associated electronic file.
